"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-05-repechage-mean-paris-2024-olympics-works-21361731\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"If you have been following the 2024OlympicsinParis, the word repechage will have been popping up all over the place.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024OlympicsinParis\", \"from\": 27, \"to\": 50}, {\"ngram\": \"the word repechage\", \"from\": 52, \"to\": 70}, {\"ngram\": \"the place\", \"from\": 106, \"to\": 115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A repechage round has been newly introduced for the Games this summer for all the individual track events, except the 100m sprint.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 248, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A repechage round\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 135}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 175}, {\"ngram\": \"all the individual track events\", \"from\": 192, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m sprint\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 247}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the 110m hurdles and 200m dash, right through to longer distance 800m and 1500m events, you will see repechage races.\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 110m hurdles\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 271}, {\"ngram\": \"200m dash\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"800m\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 324}, {\"ngram\": \"1500m events\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"repechage races\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics Organisers said it is an 'innovation' that's making its debut in the modern day Olympics.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 431}, {\"ngram\": \"an 'innovation\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 482}, {\"ngram\": \"its debut\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern day\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics president Sebastian Coe said in 2022 when the new rounds were announced: 'The repechage rounds will give more exposure to our sport during the peak Olympic period and will be carefully scheduled to ensure that every event on our Olympic programme retains its share of the spotlight.'\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999011513458, \"rank\": 9.884856115404214e-08, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new rounds\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 610}, {\"ngram\": \"The repechage rounds\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"more exposure\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"our sport\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 685}, {\"ngram\": \"the peak Olympic period\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 716}, {\"ngram\": \"every event\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"our Olympic programme\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"its share\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loosely translated from French, repechage means 'second chance'.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9811914692007689, \"rank\": 0.016784579449783288, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"repechage\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 880}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a system used in a whole host of other events, including track cycling, rowing, wrestling and speed skating, but is new to track and field for Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1053, \"end\": 1063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.220134535941325e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a system\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole host\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"other events\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"track cycling\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 980}, {\"ngram\": \"rowing\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"wrestling\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"speed skating\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a nutshell, it basically gives athletes who have been knocked out in heats and preliminary rounds a second chance at qualifying for semi-finals and finals.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a nutshell\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"heats\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"preliminary rounds\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"a second chance\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"semi\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1212}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, the top three finishers in heats would progress automatically, with the rest of the spots being filled by fourth-placed or lower runners who recorded the best times.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top three finishers\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"heats\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"the spots\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1327}, {\"ngram\": \"fourth-placed or lower runners\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1374}, {\"ngram\": \"the best times\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But now the remaining spots in finals are decided by another race between the 'best losers', called the repechage.\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the remaining spots\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"another race\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1470}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'best losers\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1495}, {\"ngram\": \"the repechage\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each race will have a certain number of pre-determined automatic qualifying positions, whether it's the top two or top three.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each race\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain number\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"pre-determined automatic qualifying positions\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next best finishers then go into the repechage race.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The next best finishers\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"the repechage race\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For those athletes, they will run one extra race.\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those athletes\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"one extra race\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, there are now four rounds in total which work as follows: World Athletics said when introducing the new system in 2022: 'As the 100m already has preliminary heats, before round one, the repechage will not be introduced in this event.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 2001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999011513458, \"rank\": 9.884856115404214e-08, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four rounds\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"the new system\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1877}, {\"ngram\": \"preliminary heats\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"the repechage\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1962}, {\"ngram\": \"this event\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1999}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'In addition, the repechage will not be introduced in distance events as the need for proper recovery between rounds makes the format impractical.'\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"the repechage\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"distance events\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngra